it is normal and necessary for the abdominal muscles to spread apart during pregnancy to make room for the growing baby there is nothing you can or need to do about this during pregnancy you should avoid movements that place a lot of strain on the straight abdominal muscles eg sitting on your side instead of the classic situp and exercises that stretch the muscles against each other ie twisting be careful in the first few weeks after birth exercises that activate the transverse abdominal muscles transversus abdominis can help them come together but in the vast majority of cases the tissue heals back together on its own whether everything heals as it should and what you can do to support it is all part of a good postnatal course

losing your drivers license which means you have to be stopped by the prf there are areas where the police are wimps and dont care about this but the law is simple you need a helmet to get on a motorcycle whether youre riding or not riding a motorcycle without a helmet increases the number of problems another thing is putting up with brutality its not uncommon for the police highway civil military or federal to be quite violent when approaching you they yell at you to get on the ground they immediately put their feet on you you have to be very patient to put up with this although its not the correct practice its common and its easier to put up with this than to complain without witnesses without a clear video recording the entire approach in genivaldos case he had schizophrenia perhaps his patience to tolerate these approaches was shorter than normal shorter than yours or mine according to witnesses genivaldo was calm at the beginning of the approach but after a certain point he wasnt anymore basically human behavior is largely a reflection of the behavior of the other human in front of you if you react rudely they will be even ruder but you cant afford that luxury you will have to put up with their rudeness if you are not committing any crime and they are not looking for horns on a horses head the rudeness will soon end and you will be released or in the case of being caught without a helmet they will take your drivers license call a tow truck for the motorcycle you sign one or two terms and then you are released this is not a crime that results in detention at most they will take you to the police station for proper identification if you are without documents or a drivers license anyone who has a short temper and argues with anyone has a high chance of getting caught by the police any day whether in traffic or even on foot but theyre more likely to be caught on a motorcycle there are a lot of undocumented motorcycles around the country driving around after being stolen or without paying all the taxes due so theyre more likely to be stopped on a motorcycle than in a car or on foot its not a question of being right or wrong in an argument its like fighting over politics there are situations where the other person is clearly wrong but its not by arguing that theyre going to believe theyre wrong its easier to just ignore it and thats it its not a question of winning arguments but of not being stupid enough to get into them
